TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—On “A Quantity Discount Pricing Model to Increase Vendor Profits”
AU  - Banerjee, Avijit
Y1  - 1986/11/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.32.11.1513
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.32.11.1513
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1513
EP  - 1517
VL  - 32
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Monahan (Monahan, James P. 1984. A quantity discount pricing model to increase vendor profits. Management Sci. 30 (June) 720?726.) develops a model for establishing an optimal quantity discount schedule from a vendor's viewpoint. In this note we show that this model is limited to the case where the vendor buys from another supplier. Incorporating vendor's inventory carrying costs, we develop a generalized version of Monahan's model and demonstrate its equivalence with the joint economic lot size approach suggested by Banerjee (Banerjee, Avijit. 1986. A joint economic lot size model for purchaser and vendor. Decision Sci. 17 (Summer) 292?311.).
AB  - Monahan (Monahan, James P. 1984. A quantity discount pricing model to increase vendor profits. Management Sci. 30 (June) 720?726.) develops a model for establishing an optimal quantity discount schedule from a vendor's viewpoint. In this note we show that this model is limited to the case where the vendor buys from another supplier. Incorporating vendor's inventory carrying costs, we develop a generalized version of Monahan's model and demonstrate its equivalence with the joint economic lot size approach suggested by Banerjee (Banerjee, Avijit. 1986. A joint economic lot size model for purchaser and vendor. Decision Sci. 17 (Summer) 292?311.).
